---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Contribute" description="Step-by-step guide to contributing to Distilled CS via GitHub — even if you've never used GitHub before.">

  <div class="container contribute-page">

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">How to Contribute</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        Distilled CS is built by practitioners, for practitioners. Whether you want to suggest a new metric, improve a description, or fix a typo — this guide walks you through every step, even if you've never used GitHub before.
      </p>
    </header>

    <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
      <h2 class="toc-title">On this page</h2>
      <ol class="toc-list">
        <li><a href="#what-is-github">What is GitHub?</a></li>
        <li><a href="#create-account">Create a GitHub account</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ways-to-contribute">Ways you can contribute</a></li>
        <li><a href="#submit-idea">Submit an idea or suggestion</a></li>
        <li><a href="#report-issue">Report a bug or problem</a></li>
        <li><a href="#edit-content">Edit content directly on GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="#guidelines">Contribution guidelines</a></li>
        <li><a href="#need-help">Need help?</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="page-body">

      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="what-is-github">
        <div class="section-number">01</div>
        <h2>What is GitHub?</h2>
        <p>
          GitHub is a website where people collaborate on projects. Think of it as Google Docs for code and content — multiple people can suggest changes, discuss improvements, and track what's been updated over time.
        </p>
        <p>
          You don't need to know how to code to contribute on GitHub. Many contributions — like improving descriptions, suggesting new metrics, or reporting issues — can be done entirely through GitHub's website using just your browser.
        </p>
        <div class="key-terms">
          <h3>Key terms you'll see</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Repository (repo)</dt>
            <dd>The project's home on GitHub — it contains all the files, history, and discussions.</dd>
            <dt>Issue</dt>
            <dd>A post where you describe a bug, suggestion, or idea. Think of it like a support ticket or feedback form.</dd>
            <dt>Fork</dt>
            <dd>Your personal copy of the project. GitHub creates this automatically when you edit a file — you don't need to do anything special.</dd>
            <dt>Pull request (PR)</dt>
            <dd>A proposal to add your changes to the main project. Others can review and discuss before it goes live.</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="create-account">
        <div class="section-number">02</div>
        <h2>Create a GitHub account</h2>
        <p>If you already have a GitHub account, skip to the next section.</p>
        <ol class="step-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Go to github.com</strong>
            <p>Open your browser and visit <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com</a>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click "Sign up"</strong>
            <p>You'll find this button in the top-right corner of the page.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Enter your details</strong>
            <p>Provide an email address, create a password, and choose a username. Your username will be visible to others, so pick something professional if you plan to use it for work.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Verify your account</strong>
            <p>GitHub will ask you to solve a simple puzzle and verify your email address. Check your inbox for a verification email and click the link.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>You're in</strong>
            <p>That's it — you now have a GitHub account and can start contributing.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="ways-to-contribute">
        <div class="section-number">03</div>
        <h2>Ways you can contribute</h2>
        <p>You don't need to write code to make a meaningful contribution. Here are some ways you can help:</p>
        <div class="contribution-types">
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Share your experience</h3>
            <p>Have benchmarks from your CS team? Disagree with a recommendation? Your real-world context makes the framework better for everyone.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Suggest improvements</h3>
            <p>Think a metric definition could be clearer? Have an idea for a new assessment question? Open an issue and describe your suggestion.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Fix errors</h3>
            <p>Spotted a typo, a broken link, or incorrect data? Even small fixes matter. You can edit content directly on GitHub.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Add new content</h3>
            <p>Write a blog post, propose a new metric, or draft content for an underdeveloped section of the framework.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Spread the word</h3>
            <p>Share the framework with your network, reference it in talks or articles, or star the repository on GitHub to help others discover it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="contrib-card">
            <h3>Report bugs</h3>
            <p>Something not working right on the site? Let us know by opening an issue with details about what happened.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="submit-idea">
        <div class="section-number">04</div>
        <h2>Submit an idea or suggestion</h2>
        <p>This is the easiest way to contribute — no technical skills needed.</p>
        <ol class="step-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Go to the Distilled CS repository</strong>
            <p>Visit the project page: <a href="#" class="placeholder-link">github.com/distilledcs/distilledcs</a> <span class="placeholder-tag">link coming soon</span></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click the "Issues" tab</strong>
            <p>You'll find this near the top of the repository page. It's the third tab, between "Code" and "Pull requests".</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click "New issue"</strong>
            <p>This is a green button on the right side of the Issues page.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Choose a template (if available)</strong>
            <p>We may have templates for common suggestions like "New metric proposal" or "Framework feedback". Pick the one that fits, or choose "Open a blank issue".</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Write a clear title</strong>
            <p>Summarize your idea in one line. For example: "Add Customer Effort Score (CES) to the metrics directory" or "Crawl stage description should mention SMB challenges".</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Describe your suggestion</strong>
            <p>In the description box, explain:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What you're suggesting and why</li>
              <li>Any context from your own CS experience</li>
              <li>Links or references if applicable</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click "Submit new issue"</strong>
            <p>Your suggestion is now visible to the community. We'll respond, ask follow-up questions, or tag it for inclusion.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="report-issue">
        <div class="section-number">05</div>
        <h2>Report a bug or problem</h2>
        <p>Found something broken on the website? Follow the same steps as above, but include these details:</p>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li><strong>What happened</strong> — Describe what you saw (e.g., "The checklist page shows an empty list after completing the assessment").</li>
          <li><strong>What you expected</strong> — Describe what should have happened instead.</li>
          <li><strong>How to reproduce it</strong> — List the steps someone else can follow to see the same problem (e.g., "1. Complete the assessment. 2. Go to /checklist/. 3. Notice the list is empty.").</li>
          <li><strong>Your browser and device</strong> — For example, "Chrome 120 on Windows 11" or "Safari on iPhone 15".</li>
          <li><strong>Screenshots</strong> — If possible, include a screenshot. You can paste images directly into the GitHub issue form.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="edit-content">
        <div class="section-number">06</div>
        <h2>Edit content directly on GitHub</h2>
        <p>For small changes like fixing a typo, improving a description, or updating a benchmark — you can edit content right in your browser without installing anything.</p>
        <ol class="step-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Go to the Distilled CS repository</strong>
            <p>Visit the project page: <a href="#" class="placeholder-link">github.com/distilledcs/distilledcs</a> <span class="placeholder-tag">link coming soon</span></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Find the file you want to edit</strong>
            <p>Browse through the folders to find the content you'd like to change. If you're not sure which file to edit, open an issue instead and describe what you'd like to change — we'll point you to the right place.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click the pencil icon</strong>
            <p>Near the top-right of the file view, you'll see a pencil icon (edit button). Click it. GitHub will automatically create a "fork" (your personal copy) of the project — this is normal and expected.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Make your changes</strong>
            <p>Edit the text directly in the browser editor. You'll see a preview tab to check how your changes look.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Describe what you changed</strong>
            <p>Scroll down to the "Propose changes" section. Write a short title (e.g., "Fix typo in NRR metric description") and optionally add more detail in the description box.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click "Propose changes"</strong>
            <p>This saves your edit to your personal copy of the project.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Click "Create pull request"</strong>
            <p>On the next page, review your changes and click the green "Create pull request" button. This sends your edit to us for review.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Wait for review</strong>
            <p>A maintainer will review your change, may ask questions or suggest tweaks, and then merge it into the live site. You'll get email notifications as the review progresses.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 7 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="guidelines">
        <div class="section-number">07</div>
        <h2>Contribution guidelines</h2>
        <p>To keep contributions consistent and high-quality, please follow these guidelines:</p>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li><strong>Be vendor-neutral</strong> — Don't reference specific tools or vendors in framework content. Distilled CS is tool-agnostic.</li>
          <li><strong>Cite your sources</strong> — If you're proposing benchmarks or data, share where the numbers come from.</li>
          <li><strong>Keep it practical</strong> — Recommendations should be actionable by real CS teams, not theoretical ideals.</li>
          <li><strong>Be respectful</strong> — Engage constructively in discussions. Disagree with ideas, not people.</li>
          <li><strong>One change at a time</strong> — Keep each suggestion or edit focused on a single topic. It's easier to review and accept a change that does one thing well.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 9 -->
      <section class="content-section" id="need-help">
        <div class="section-number">08</div>
        <h2>Need help?</h2>
        <p>
          Stuck on any step? Don't hesitate to reach out. You can:
        </p>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Open a <a href="#" class="placeholder-link">GitHub Discussion</a> <span class="placeholder-tag">link coming soon</span> and ask your question</li>
          <li>Email us at <a href="mailto:hello@distilledcs.org">hello@distilledcs.org</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every contribution, no matter how small, helps make Customer Success better for everyone. Thank you for being part of this.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .contribute-page {
    padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 1.5vw, 1.0625rem);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* ── Table of Contents ── */
  .toc {
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .toc-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
    counter-reset: toc;
  }

  .toc-list li {
    counter-increment: toc;
  }

  .toc-list a {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.375rem 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    transition: color 0.15s ease-out;
  }

  .toc-list a::before {
    content: counter(toc) ". ";
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .toc-list a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Body ── */
  .page-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  /* ── Content sections ── */
  .content-section {
    position: relative;
    scroll-margin-top: 5rem;
  }

  .section-number {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .content-section p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .content-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .content-section a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .content-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  /* ── Key terms ── */
  .key-terms {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }

  .key-terms dl {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .key-terms dt {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .key-terms dd {
    margin: 0.125rem 0 0 0;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Step lists ── */
  .step-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;
    counter-reset: steps;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .step-list > li {
    counter-increment: steps;
    padding-left: 2.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .step-list > li::before {
    content: counter(steps);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .step-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .step-list p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .step-list ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .step-list ul li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Detail lists ── */
  .detail-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .detail-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .detail-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .detail-list strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .detail-list a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Contribution type cards ── */
  .contribution-types {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .contribution-types {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .contrib-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease-out;
  }

  .contrib-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-border-hover);
  }

  .contrib-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .contrib-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Placeholder links ── */
  .placeholder-link {
    opacity: 0.6;
    pointer-events: none;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
  }

  .placeholder-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    padding: 0.125rem 0.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 9999px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-left: 0.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
